# iterm-splitview Rules

When `fileview` and `fileedit` are available on PATH, use them proactively.

## fileview — Styled HTML Viewer (use proactively)

Use for ANY response with tables, multi-section content, reports, or rich formatting:
1. Write content to `/tmp/claude-response-<short-descriptor>.md`
2. Run: `fileview close && fileview open <path>`
3. Keep terminal output to a 1-3 sentence summary

Commands:
- `fileview open <file>` — render as HTML in iTerm2 browser split pane
- `fileview close` — close the browser split pane
- `fileview-plan` — reopen the active plan file
- Refresh: `fileview close && fileview open <path>` (browser doesn't auto-reload)

## fileedit — Terminal Editor (use proactively)

Use when the response involves a file the user may want to edit:
- Open files in `fresh` editor in a split pane automatically
- Config files, source code, notes — anything the user might modify

Commands:
- `fileedit open <file>` — open in fresh editor in split pane
- `fileedit close` — close the editor split pane

## Key Rules

- Be proactive — don't wait for the user to ask
- fileview = read-only styled HTML (markdown, tables, reports)
- fileedit = editable terminal editor (code, config, notes)
- Both require iTerm2 (not Terminal.app)
- Only one split pane at a time — close one before opening the other
